Missingness First Impression

Based on the missingness pattern heatmap, we can tell, some observations have abnormally consistent missing values. Those observations are likely to have missingness for most of their input values. Thus, the above missingness proportion per observation table was generated, and only subjects with missing proportion ârisks_missing_prop_obs > 0 OR total_missing_prop_obs > 0.095â were shown in the table. The risks_missing_prop_obs is the measurement of missingness for 20 risks columns and 7 risk rejections cols. The total_missing_prop_obs is the measurement of overall missingness including more than 500 columns.
